Twenty minutes can't be too late.
Valerie, please.

238
00:16:50,858 --> 00:16:53,942
Don't let 20 minutes stand in
the way of what I'm trying to do.

239
00:16:54,025 --> 00:16:56,317
- Please don't start.
- Don't talk to him.

240
00:16:56,401 --> 00:16:58,484
Mr. Gipson, would you please
approach the bench?

241
00:16:58,568 --> 00:17:00,653
- Your Honor, can we leave now?
- Yes.

242
00:17:00,695 --> 00:17:02,445
- Mr. Gipson-
- Valerie, can't we talk?

243
00:17:02,529 --> 00:17:04,445
- Valerie, can we-
- Mr. Gipson.

244
00:17:04,529 --> 00:17:07,448
Mr. Gipson, come here for a moment.
Please?

245
00:17:09,365 --> 00:17:12,368
Emotions run high in here.
If this weren't a divorce court...

246
00:17:12,450 --> 00:17:14,117
the way you just yelled
in my courtroom-

247
00:17:14,201 --> 00:17:16,118
- I'm sorry.
- Of course you are.

248
00:17:16,202 --> 00:17:19,494
You have children, Mr. Gipson.
Keep them in front of you.

249
00:17:19,578 --> 00:17:23,080
I just wanted to tell my wife
I got her a house for the children.

250
00:17:23,163 --> 00:17:25,831
- When?
- Well, I have it all right here.

251
00:17:25,914 --> 00:17:29,583
That's my plan. I found a house
for Valerie and for the boys...

252
00:17:29,667 --> 00:17:31,750
and they don't have to move.

253
00:17:31,834 --> 00:17:36,795
This is what I wanted to say.
"Boys need their fathers.

254
00:17:36,878 --> 00:17:41,340
The streets of this world are lonely
for boys without their fathers.

255
00:17:41,423 --> 00:17:44,006
I have made mistakes,
and I have grown...

256
00:17:44,048 --> 00:17:47,841
and I have recognized
those mistakes."

257
00:17:47,925 --> 00:17:50,801
What kind of a house?

258
00:17:50,884 --> 00:17:53,427
It's not a big house,
and it's not in great shape.

259
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:55,429
But I can fix it.
I can make it work.

260
00:17:55,511 --> 00:17:58,971
And there's a space for-

261
00:17:59,054 --> 00:18:02,515
Well, if she'll have me back,
there's a place for me too.

262
00:18:02,598 --> 00:18:05,392
But I'm not asking for that
right now. I'm just asking that...

263
00:18:05,475 --> 00:18:08,144
she not take the boys and move
halfway across the world.

264
00:18:08,227 --> 00:18:12,270
You can arrange visitations. Oregon
is not the other side of the world.

265
00:18:12,353 --> 00:18:15,813
It is to me!
I want my family. I want my boys.

266
00:18:15,896 --> 00:18:19,398
I had an accident.
This guy hit me on the FDR.

267
00:18:19,482 --> 00:18:22,691
He cut me off!
I wanted to be here!

268
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:25,776
If this was my marriage,
I would've been here on time.

269
00:18:25,859 --> 00:18:29,359
Everyone was here on time,
except you. Next case.

270
00:18:29,443 --> 00:18:30,694
Thank you.

271
00:18:32,278 --> 00:18:34,530
- Docket 718.
- Thanks.

272
00:18:34,571 --> 00:18:37,447
Counselor, step up, please.

273
00:18:37,530 --> 00:18:39,948
- How is everybody today?
- Good morning, Your Honor.

274
00:18:40,032 --> 00:18:41,491
Nice to see you again.

275
00:18:59,582 --> 00:19:03,418
It's not gonna help me pay
my phone bill, my electric bill.

276
00:19:03,502 --> 00:19:05,752
I'm not making any money sittin'
in court. I'm goin' to court.

277
00:19:05,835 --> 00:19:09,504
I've been sittin' in court every
day. I'm not making any money.

278
00:20:03,820 --> 00:20:08,071
If you and I had gotten caught
before we stopped...

279
00:20:10,324 --> 00:20:14,241
and my wife found out,
and I left the law...

280
00:20:15,283 --> 00:20:18,285
and you died in
a horrible accident at sea...

281
00:20:19,910 --> 00:20:23,370
I would be better off
than I am right now.

282
00:20:23,454 --> 00:20:24,872
What happened?

283
00:20:27,248 --> 00:20:28,707
He wouldn't take a check.

284
00:20:28,790 --> 00:20:32,667
He said he wanted to be clean
in all his actions.

285
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:35,793
- The judge wouldn't take a check?
- The guy.

286
00:20:35,877 --> 00:20:36,877
What guy?

287
00:20:36,961 --> 00:20:38,586
- What day is today?
- Friday.

288
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:41,754
- Actually, it's Good Friday.
- Good Friday.

289
00:20:41,795 --> 00:20:44,339
- What's good about it?
- Gavin, what's going on?

290
00:20:44,422 --> 00:20:47,006
I know what's good about it.

291
00:20:47,090 --> 00:20:48,924
My file's walking down the street.

292
00:20:56,511 --> 00:20:58,971
Hey! Excuse me.

293
00:20:59,055 --> 00:21:01,139
Listen, man, you don't know me.
I know.

294
00:21:01,222 --> 00:21:05,348
And you don't have to believe me,
but that was not like me today.

295
00:21:05,432 --> 00:21:09,100
And I'm just so grateful,
you know, to God...

296
00:21:09,183 --> 00:21:12,351
and right here in front
of the Lord's house.

297
00:21:12,434 --> 00:21:14,978
Come on. Hop in. Get in the car.
Get out of the rain.

298
00:21:17,312 --> 00:21:19,230
My name's Gavin Banek.

299
00:21:22,982 --> 00:21:25,733
- Doyle Gipson.
- Hey, listen, Doyle.

300
00:21:25,817 --> 00:21:27,985
That is not what I'm like-
this morning.

301
00:21:28,068 --> 00:21:30,485
That's not who I am.
I mean it. I'm a lawyer.

302
00:21:30,569 --> 00:21:32,110
I should have never left
the scene of an accident.

303
00:21:32,193 --> 00:21:35,028
I should know better.

304
00:21:37,779 --> 00:21:39,697
My file- did you fllnd it?

305
00:21:40,947 --> 00:21:45,366
I had an orange file.
It was in my briefcase.

306
00:21:45,450 --> 00:21:49,410
I thought may be it fell out
and you picked it up.

307
00:21:50,828 --> 00:21:52,244
Do you have it?
Did you get it?

308
00:21:54,162 --> 00:21:56,913
You said,
"Better luck next time."

309
00:21:56,996 --> 00:21:58,956
I said, "Give me a lift."
You said...

310
00:21:59,039 --> 00:22:01,124
"Better luck next time,"
and just-

311
00:22:04,541 --> 00:22:06,751
"Better luck next time"?
I said that?

312
00:22:06,834 --> 00:22:09,085
Listen, sir, please.

313
00:22:09,168 --> 00:22:12,587
I have no excuse for my behavior,
and I am sorry.

314
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:14,796
I don't know what I can do
to make it up to you, except-

315
00:22:14,838 --> 00:22:16,757
I will buy you a new car.

316
00:22:20,007 --> 00:22:24,052
Money. You think I want money?

317
00:22:24,134 --> 00:22:27,677
What I want is my morning back.

318
00:22:27,761 --> 00:22:30,971
I need you to give
my time back to me.

319
00:22:31,054 --> 00:22:33,139
Can you give me back my time?

320
00:22:33,222 --> 00:22:37,223
Can you give my time back to me?
Huh? Can you?

321
00:22:37,306 --> 00:22:40,433
Whoa! Wait a minute!
Whoa! All right!

322
00:22:40,516 --> 00:22:43,227
So she won't move to Oregon!
So she won't take the boys!

323
00:22:43,310 --> 00:22:46,520
So they'll move into the house
so I can be a father!

324
00:22:46,603 --> 00:22:49,063
Just 20 minutes!
Can you give me that?

325
00:22:49,146 --> 00:22:51,564
I wish I could, man.
I wish I could.

326
00:22:53,856 --> 00:22:55,774
I wish I could.

327
00:22:58,608 --> 00:23:00,985
Wait a minute!
Wait. Do you have the file?

328
00:23:01,027 --> 00:23:03,527
Doyle, you got the file?

329
00:23:03,611 --> 00:23:05,527
Wait a minute! Doyle!
Wait a minute!

330
00:23:05,611 --> 00:23:07,528
Doyle, do you have the file?

331
00:23:07,570 --> 00:23:09,571
- I'm sorry!
- I don't have your file!

332
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:11,740
- I threw it away!
- What do you mean?

333
00:23:11,822 --> 00:23:13,741
I threw it away!

334
00:24:01,721 --> 00:24:03,638
- Hey, guys.
- How did it go?

335
00:24:08,933 --> 00:24:12,684
Well, Kaufman did some tap dancing.

336
00:24:14,561 --> 00:24:18,186
But once I filed the papers,
what was he gonna do?

337
00:24:18,270 --> 00:24:20,437
The guy squeaked like a mouse.

338
00:24:20,521 --> 00:24:22,480
I love it when they squeak.

339
00:24:23,648 --> 00:24:26,857
We have the power of appointment,
so God's on our side.

340
00:24:30,234 --> 00:24:33,193
Hey, I'm going over
to Southeast Harbor tomorrow...

341
00:24:33,235 --> 00:24:35,528
to look at a boat.

342
00:24:35,611 --> 00:24:36,736
Hinckley 51.

343
00:24:36,820 --> 00:24:40,071
Wow. Fifty-one footer, huh?
It's a tough life.

344
00:24:40,155 --> 00:24:42,530
You are not quite ready
for a 51-footer yet.

345
00:24:42,572 --> 00:24:44,364
Oh, right.

346
00:24:44,448 --> 00:24:46,908
But as soon as
I take delivery on her...

347
00:24:46,949 --> 00:24:50,617
I want you and Cynthia
to have China Bird.

348
00:24:57,745 --> 00:25:01,081
- Steven, I don't know what to say.
- You don't have to say anything.

349
00:25:01,164 --> 00:25:04,458
I'm saying thank you to my partner
and my son-in-law...

350
00:25:07,792 --> 00:25:09,376
and my friend.

351
00:25:12,336 --> 00:25:15,546
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

352
00:25:15,588 --> 00:25:17,880
Thank you.

353
00:25:20,590 --> 00:25:22,131
Thank you.

354
00:25:23,091 --> 00:25:26,301
So I have a couple more interviews
I gotta bang out...

355
00:25:26,384 --> 00:25:28,552
down the hall, so I'm gonna...

356
00:25:28,635 --> 00:25:30,762
go back down there
and do some work.

357
00:25:30,845 --> 00:25:32,637
Great.

358
00:25:36,514 --> 00:25:38,639
All right, well, so long.

359
00:25:38,723 --> 00:25:41,183
- See you.
- All right.

360
00:25:49,437 --> 00:25:51,395
- How are you doing, Kate?
- Hey, Gavin.

361
00:25:56,064 --> 00:25:58,900
- So, how'd it go?
- In and out. Easy-peasy.

362
00:25:58,942 --> 00:26:03,318
- What kind of people have we here?
- This is Sarah Windsor.

363
00:26:03,402 --> 00:26:04,778
Hello. It's a pleasure.

364
00:26:04,861 --> 00:26:08,570
- Tyler Cohen.
- How are you? Who's up first?

365
00:26:08,653 --> 00:26:11,613
- Miss Windsor.
- Sarah Windsor, come on down!

366
00:26:11,696 --> 00:26:13,947
Have a seat, please.

367
00:26:14,030 --> 00:26:17,490
- And who are you?
- Sarah Windsor.

368
00:26:17,573 --> 00:26:20,992
Not the name tag. Who are you,
as in what have you been doing?

369
00:26:21,075 --> 00:26:23,118
Why do you wanna be a lawyer?
Why do you wanna work here?

370
00:26:23,201 --> 00:26:26,161
Well, I went to St. Paul's.

371
00:26:26,244 --> 00:26:28,578
I did my undergraduate work at Yale.

372
00:26:28,620 --> 00:26:31,122
And now, I'm finishing at Yale Law.

373
00:26:31,205 --> 00:26:35,665
I clerked last summer for
the California State Supreme Court.

374
00:26:35,748 --> 00:26:39,500
I chose law because my father was
district attorney of San Francisco.

375
00:26:39,583 --> 00:26:40,500
Really?

376
00:26:40,584 --> 00:26:42,668
I've always been interested
in the law and politics...

377
00:26:42,752 --> 00:26:46,378
and I was an economics major.

378
00:26:46,462 --> 00:26:48,337
This firm is particularly strong...

379
00:26:48,421 --> 00:26:51,256
in municipal finance law
and public policy...

380
00:26:51,298 --> 00:26:56,842
which is the area
I'm hoping to explore.

381
00:26:56,925 --> 00:26:59,093
Although, I gotta tell you...

382
00:26:59,135 --> 00:27:01,511
I do have an eye on public service.

383
00:27:02,344 --> 00:27:04,929
I know how much this firm
supports pro bono work...

384
00:27:05,013 --> 00:27:08,889
and I'd love to help on a
death penalty defense for the poor.

385
00:27:15,434 --> 00:27:17,643
Why didn't I just
give him my insurance card?

386
00:27:17,727 --> 00:27:19,353
I'm sorry?

387
00:27:19,436 --> 00:27:23,271
I'm sorry. It's not your fault.
It's my fault.

388
00:27:24,313 --> 00:27:25,939
Excuse me. Gavin?

389
00:27:25,981 --> 00:27:28,065
This really weird fax
Just came in.

390
00:27:28,149 --> 00:27:30,774
- I think you should look at it.
- Okay. Thank you.

391
00:27:32,483 --> 00:27:34,818
Do you know what it means?

392
00:27:43,154 --> 00:27:46,614
Michelle, I gotta talk to you.

393
00:27:46,656 --> 00:27:48,449
Just a second.
What the hell-

394
00:27:48,533 --> 00:27:50,283
Read this!

395
00:27:50,367 --> 00:27:53,367
It's from the file.
He's got the file.

396
00:27:59,328 --> 00:28:01,371
Help me.

397
00:28:16,337 --> 00:28:18,255
Can I have a...

398
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:26,090
- bourbon, straight up?
- Sure.

399
00:28:44,683 --> 00:28:46,602
Can I have a twist, please?

400
00:29:00,232 --> 00:29:01,649
I'm not a partner here.

401
00:29:01,691 --> 00:29:04,316
That actually doesn't bother me.

402
00:29:04,358 --> 00:29:07,485
Partners have to bring in business.
I just gotta do my job.

403
00:29:07,527 --> 00:29:09,486
If I don't like it here,
I can leave.

404
00:29:10,904 --> 00:29:14,238
- What's not to like?
- Watching you become one of them.

405
00:29:17,614 --> 00:29:20,489
I always thought you were cutting
a pretty big corner...

406
00:29:20,573 --> 00:29:23,617
by convincing a dying old man
to sign a power of appointment.

407
00:29:23,701 --> 00:29:26,243
- It wasn't like that.
- Are you sure it wasn't like that?

408
00:29:26,325 --> 00:29:28,411
Of course I'm sure.

409
00:29:34,872 --> 00:29:36,498
What?

410
00:29:39,541 --> 00:29:41,834
He was in pretty bad shape
when I went to see him.

411
00:29:41,918 --> 00:29:44,335
I mean, it was-
May be he didn't-

412
00:29:44,377 --> 00:29:46,252
May be?

413
00:29:46,336 --> 00:29:50,588
- May be he didn't understand exactly.
- Didn't understand exactly?

414
00:29:50,671 --> 00:29:53,172
He didn't know exactly
what he was signing.

415
00:29:53,256 --> 00:29:56,632
Walter and Steven said that...

416
00:29:56,715 --> 00:30:00,592
Simon put too much faith
in his friends, and...

417
00:30:00,675 --> 00:30:04,261
the board was in his pocket, and
it was better for the foundation...

418
00:30:04,344 --> 00:30:06,512
if we could just help
control and manage the money.

419
00:30:06,596 --> 00:30:08,638
Delano said that?

420
00:30:08,722 --> 00:30:10,972
- Doesn't that sound reasonable?
- What's that supposed to mean?

421
00:30:11,056 --> 00:30:13,474
That means that
without this file...

422
00:30:13,557 --> 00:30:16,975
you'll be in more trouble than
your father-in-law and his partner.

423
00:30:17,058 --> 00:30:19,727
You're the attorney of record.

424
00:30:19,809 --> 00:30:22,227
You could actually
go to jail for this.

425
00:30:22,310 --> 00:30:24,062
You need that file.

426
00:30:24,937 --> 00:30:26,895
What am I gonna do?

427
00:30:33,983 --> 00:30:35,526
There's this guy.

428
00:30:37,485 --> 00:30:42,404
He helps out
with things that need...

429
00:30:42,446 --> 00:30:43,654
helping out.

430
00:30:44,571 --> 00:30:45,780
Like what?

431
00:30:47,155 --> 00:30:50,573
Like things. Like...

432
00:30:50,614 --> 00:30:52,699
getting people to do things
you want them to do...

433
00:30:52,740 --> 00:30:56,492
when they don't necessarily
want to do them.

434
00:30:58,743 --> 00:31:01,078
Where is he?

435
00:31:08,582 --> 00:31:10,458
I need help.

436
00:31:10,541 --> 00:31:12,291
Did you really believe
that it served Simon Dunne...

437
00:31:12,374 --> 00:31:14,542
to sign those papers when
he was too weak to read them?

438
00:31:14,584 --> 00:31:16,918
I wouldn't have done it otherwise.
Yes.

439
00:31:19,003 --> 00:31:22,379
- Yes, I did.
- Do you want what's right?

440
00:31:22,421 --> 00:31:24,547
Of course I do.

441
00:31:24,589 --> 00:31:29,050
And what's right is your job,
your wife...

442
00:31:29,133 --> 00:31:30,426
your life?

443
00:31:41,597 --> 00:31:43,765
Where is he?

444
00:31:53,352 --> 00:31:55,311
Don't go anywhere.

445
00:31:55,395 --> 00:31:58,230
- Hey, where are you going?
- I'm going out.

446
00:32:00,899 --> 00:32:02,690
I'm in a bar.

447
00:32:03,857 --> 00:32:05,442
You want company?

448
00:32:08,526 --> 00:32:10,944
That champagne feeling
gave you a hangover.

449
00:32:12,236 --> 00:32:14,654
Are you drinking?

450
00:32:24,407 --> 00:32:26,909
What happened in court today?

451
00:32:26,992 --> 00:32:29,201
I'm in a bar.
What's that tell you?

452
00:32:29,284 --> 00:32:33,578
It tells me that you're really
angry, and that anger...

453
00:32:33,620 --> 00:32:36,496
has gotten you into the one place
in the world you shouldn't be.

454
00:32:40,290 --> 00:32:42,541
Come on.
Leave that bar.

455
00:32:46,375 --> 00:32:48,293
Come on.
Leave the bar.

456
00:32:51,963 --> 00:32:53,379
I'm sorry.

457
00:33:29,605 --> 00:33:31,606
Can I have a Coke, please?

458
00:33:40,610 --> 00:33:42,610
Come on in.

459
00:33:42,693 --> 00:33:44,820
Look, you tell Roberta...

460
00:33:44,903 --> 00:33:48,948
that I said one cookie
before lunch is okay.

461
00:33:49,990 --> 00:33:51,990
Get better.

462
00:33:52,032 --> 00:33:54,365
- Mr. Banek.
- Are you Mr. Finch?

463
00:33:54,449 --> 00:33:56,366
- How are you?
- How are you doing?

464
00:33:58,367 --> 00:34:02,286
- You look nervous.
- Yeah, a little bit.

465
00:34:02,369 --> 00:34:04,494
Don't be.
Have a seat.

466
00:34:06,829 --> 00:34:09,830
Who's your God?

467
00:34:09,914 --> 00:34:13,249
- Now, or hall of fame?
- Whenever.

468
00:34:13,333 --> 00:34:16,918
Well, I'd say it's the guy
who did the Volkswagen ad.

469
00:34:17,001 --> 00:34:19,170
The one where the cop is giving the
speeding ticket to a guy in a Bug.

470
00:34:19,253 --> 00:34:21,169
Classic.

471
00:34:21,253 --> 00:34:23,755
Doyle Gipson.

472
00:34:23,838 --> 00:34:25,754
Shouldn't have told you
he was in insurance.

473
00:34:25,838 --> 00:34:27,797
Makes it too easy.
I tell my clients...

474
00:34:27,839 --> 00:34:31,090
"Never tell anyone anything
a bout yourself."

475
00:34:32,674 --> 00:34:36,093
Yeah. Here's his
state insurance license.

476
00:34:36,176 --> 00:34:38,719
And that gives me
his social security number...

477
00:34:38,802 --> 00:34:43,013
which gives me everything.

478
00:34:43,096 --> 00:34:45,014
- You don't fucking know.
- I do know.

479
