01:14:46,483 --> 01:14:48,569
And then another man-
you don't know him-

963
01:14:48,610 --> 01:14:51,028
he wants to help
the fllrst guy, okay?

964
01:14:51,110 --> 01:14:55,238
Now, what does he have to do to help
the second guy take out a loan?

965
01:14:55,322 --> 01:14:58,907
Come on. What do I do? Just cosign?
What's the thing? What's the deal?

966
01:14:58,949 --> 01:15:00,907
Can you please tell me
what I gotta do.

967
01:15:00,949 --> 01:15:03,284
I'm asking you what I have to do
to make this thing work.

968
01:15:05,201 --> 01:15:08,535
You know this has nothing
to do with you. It's this guy.

969
01:15:08,619 --> 01:15:11,912
- He's been at me all day.
- Some body you're fighting with?

970
01:15:11,995 --> 01:15:14,080
You had a fight with some body
who hit your car...

971
01:15:14,164 --> 01:15:16,206
and then you spent the day
in some kind of battle with him.

972
01:15:16,290 --> 01:15:18,956
Then he went to the school
to hurt you as hard as he could.

973
01:15:19,040 --> 01:15:21,959
You believe me?
Thank God. Thank God.

974
01:15:22,042 --> 01:15:24,294
This guy, this lawyer,
Gavin Banek-

975
01:15:24,377 --> 01:15:27,127
Doyle, stop! Stop, Doyle!
I don't care.

976
01:15:27,211 --> 01:15:29,544
Whatever this little drama
you've gotten yourself into...

977
01:15:29,628 --> 01:15:32,672
it's just the kind of thing
that always happens to you.

978
01:15:32,755 --> 01:15:35,923
And it never happens to me unless
I am in your field of gravity.

979
01:15:35,964 --> 01:15:39,257
You went crazy like you always do,
like you always will go crazy.

980
01:15:39,340 --> 01:15:41,884
Drunk or sober, it doesn't matter,
'cause that's you.

981
01:15:42,926 --> 01:15:45,134
A person can be loving...

982
01:15:45,218 --> 01:15:47,135
and a person can be crazy
all at once.

983
01:15:47,219 --> 01:15:50,805
That's life. But this is not
Just my life now or yours.

984
01:15:50,888 --> 01:15:53,431
It is the life
of two children...

985
01:15:53,473 --> 01:15:55,473
and I have to protect
those two children.

986
01:15:55,557 --> 01:15:58,600
Is that a misunderstanding?
Is it?

987
01:15:58,683 --> 01:16:01,267
Is it, Doyle? I mean,
is that this guy's fault?

988
01:16:03,894 --> 01:16:05,812
At least let me say
good- bye to them.

989
01:16:07,978 --> 01:16:10,271
I'm takin' those boys away,
and you will never see them again.

990
01:16:10,313 --> 01:16:14,232
You will never find us. Do not try
to come after us. Do you hear me?

991
01:16:14,315 --> 01:16:16,107
It is over!

992
01:17:02,253 --> 01:17:05,463
- Where's Ellen?
- She went home.

993
01:17:05,547 --> 01:17:07,797
Why are you still here?

994
01:17:09,006 --> 01:17:11,091
You told me to wait.

995
01:17:15,969 --> 01:17:18,345
Well, come on in.

996
01:17:24,264 --> 01:17:25,847
Have a seat.

997
01:17:33,477 --> 01:17:37,477
- So why do you wanna be a lawyer?
- I believe in the law.

998
01:17:37,561 --> 01:17:40,229
I believe in order and justice.

999
01:17:40,313 --> 01:17:43,398
I believe that people are,
by nature, good.

1000
01:17:43,481 --> 01:17:47,233
I believe that historical forces
push us into conflict...

1001
01:17:47,316 --> 01:17:50,860
and without the law
as a buffer between people...

1002
01:17:50,944 --> 01:17:54,027
we would have
a world of vendetta...

1003
01:17:54,111 --> 01:17:56,279
a world of violence,
a world of chaos.

1004
01:17:58,863 --> 01:18:01,657
The law-
The law keeps us civilized.

1005
01:18:01,740 --> 01:18:04,657
- I'm sorry.
- I don't think it's-

1006
01:18:05,658 --> 01:18:09,035
- I'm sorry.
- I don't think it's funny.

1007
01:18:09,118 --> 01:18:11,912
That's why I am gonna
give you this job.

1008
01:18:14,412 --> 01:18:18,373
Because I wanna hear what
you have to say about the law...

1009
01:18:18,456 --> 01:18:20,915
after you've worked here
for five years...

1010
01:18:20,998 --> 01:18:23,958
or three years, or a month...

1011
01:18:24,042 --> 01:18:26,043
a week, a day, an hour.

1012
01:18:29,503 --> 01:18:31,127
I'm hired?

1013
01:18:31,211 --> 01:18:33,252
Don't I have to see...

1014
01:18:33,336 --> 01:18:35,921
a committee or something?

1015
01:18:38,256 --> 01:18:41,175
- You made bail.
- Who?

1016
01:18:41,258 --> 01:18:42,841
A friend.

1017
01:18:46,093 --> 01:18:48,885
"To the Honorable
Judge Frances Abarbanel.

1018
01:18:48,969 --> 01:18:51,345
I have been unable to recover
the power of appointment...

1019
01:18:51,429 --> 01:18:53,053
signed by Simon Dunne.

1020
01:18:53,095 --> 01:18:55,555
But even if I had been able to
produce the power of appointment...

1021
01:18:55,597 --> 01:18:59,515
I want the court to know that
the document was a fraud.

1022
01:18:59,599 --> 01:19:01,474
I induced Mr. Dunne
to sign a document...

1023
01:19:01,558 --> 01:19:04,101
when his mental status was
diminished and he was incapable...

1024
01:19:04,185 --> 01:19:06,728
of making an informed decision."

1025
01:19:10,604 --> 01:19:13,648
They set you up! They made
hundreds of thousands of dollars.

1026
01:19:13,731 --> 01:19:15,898
- And they're gonna make more.
- And I made partner...

1027
01:19:15,982 --> 01:19:18,024
and a bonus that could've paid
for 200 pianos.

1028
01:19:18,108 --> 01:19:19,651
You don't say anything about them.

1029
01:19:19,733 --> 01:19:23,360
You're taking everything
on your shoulder in this letter.

1030
01:19:23,443 --> 01:19:25,527
Why? You could send 'em to jail.

1031
01:19:26,944 --> 01:19:29,029
They gotta write their own letters.

1032
01:19:54,790 --> 01:19:56,375
Let me go.

1033
01:20:18,384 --> 01:20:20,678
Should've left me inside.

1034
01:20:20,761 --> 01:20:24,554
You're too important to me.
Come on. Let's go to a meeting.

1035
01:20:24,638 --> 01:20:26,639
No, no, no.
I went to one yesterday.

1036
01:20:28,723 --> 01:20:32,516
- Well, that was yesterday.
- Yeah, one day at a time, right?

1037
01:20:32,600 --> 01:20:35,268
Yeah, one day at a time,
and do the next right thing.

1038
01:20:35,351 --> 01:20:38,227
Let's go.
There's a meeting at 6:00.

1039
01:20:38,310 --> 01:20:40,353
"God, grant me the strength...

1040
01:20:40,437 --> 01:20:43,189
to accept the things
I cannot change."

1041
01:20:54,986 --> 01:20:57,570
It's an admirable gesture,
but it's unnecessary.

1042
01:20:57,653 --> 01:21:01,071
It's unnecessary because
you've already filed...

1043
01:21:01,154 --> 01:21:03,073
the power of appointment
with the court.

1044
01:21:06,990 --> 01:21:10,451
A bonded courier delivered it
to the judge just before 5:00...

1045
01:21:10,492 --> 01:21:12,452
and her bailiff signed for it.

1046
01:21:13,743 --> 01:21:17,745
Your note of apology was contrite,
but it was absolutely professional.

1047
01:21:17,829 --> 01:21:19,746
Everything's taken care of.

1048
01:21:22,623 --> 01:21:24,541
- You filed a forgery.
- Bullshit.

1049
01:21:24,624 --> 01:21:26,709
I filed what I had to file.
What happened to-

1050
01:21:26,792 --> 01:21:29,293
You just disappeared.
Time was up.

1051
01:21:29,376 --> 01:21:31,794
Come on.
You scared the hell out of us.

1052
01:21:31,836 --> 01:21:33,794
I didn't know what to do.

1053
01:21:39,504 --> 01:21:41,423
So you finally hit rock bottom?

1054
01:21:44,924 --> 01:21:47,800
Today you almost killed a guy.
Tomorrow you might go all the way.

1055
01:21:47,842 --> 01:21:49,926
Keep doing the next wrong thing,
you could start a religion.

1056
01:21:50,010 --> 01:21:52,052
Convince the so ber to drink.
Don't tell them...

1057
01:21:52,136 --> 01:21:54,096
to keep each other alive with hope.

1058
01:21:54,179 --> 01:21:58,973
You saw today that everything decent
is held together by a covenant.

1059
01:21:59,056 --> 01:22:01,183
An agreement not to go bat shit!

1060
01:22:03,016 --> 01:22:05,893
- You broke the contract!
- I didn't have a drink!

1061
01:22:05,976 --> 01:22:07,768
Well, wow!
Thank you for sharing!

1062
01:22:07,851 --> 01:22:10,061
You didn't have a drink today!
What an inspiration!

1063
01:22:10,144 --> 01:22:12,270
That's the point, isn't it?

1064
01:22:13,854 --> 01:22:15,312
God!

1065
01:22:21,692 --> 01:22:26,152
You know, booze isn't really
your drug of choice anyway.

1066
01:22:29,028 --> 01:22:30,737
You're addicted to chaos.

1067
01:22:33,489 --> 01:22:36,281
For some of us, it's coke.
For some of us, it's bourbon.

1068
01:22:36,364 --> 01:22:38,908
But you,
you got hooked on disaster.

1069
01:22:48,371 --> 01:22:49,747
Fuck!

1070
01:22:53,748 --> 01:22:55,624
Here's what you should do.

1071
01:22:55,708 --> 01:22:58,042
You get up Monday morning...

1072
01:22:58,125 --> 01:23:00,460
and you get yourself
on a plane to Texas.

1073
01:23:00,543 --> 01:23:02,835
Take that letter with you.

1074
01:23:02,919 --> 01:23:05,378
When you get to Texas...

1075
01:23:05,461 --> 01:23:08,588
you get on the defense team
of somebody on death row.

1076
01:23:10,421 --> 01:23:14,840
And then put all your energy
into saving a man from execution.

1077
01:23:16,216 --> 01:23:19,801
And then come on back here
in a few months.

1078
01:23:19,884 --> 01:23:23,928
You still wanna confess, go ahead.

1079
01:23:25,929 --> 01:23:27,930
Come on.

1080
01:23:28,013 --> 01:23:30,389
How the hell do you think
Simon Dunne got his money?

1081
01:23:34,099 --> 01:23:36,891
You think those factories
in Malaysia...

1082
01:23:36,975 --> 01:23:38,768
have day-care centers in them?

1083
01:23:38,851 --> 01:23:42,395
Wanna check the pollution levels
of his chemical plants in Mexico...

1084
01:23:42,479 --> 01:23:46,939
or look at the tax benefllts
he got from this foundation?

1085
01:23:50,399 --> 01:23:54,525
This is all a tightrope.

1086
01:23:54,567 --> 01:23:57,444
You gotta learn to balance.

1087
01:23:57,528 --> 01:23:59,527
How can you live like that?

1088
01:23:59,611 --> 01:24:04,112
I can live with myself
because at the end of the day...

1089
01:24:04,196 --> 01:24:08,532
I think I do more good than harm.

1090
01:24:11,909 --> 01:24:15,076
What other standard
have I got to judge by?

1091
01:25:07,142 --> 01:25:09,143
I have to thank you.

1092
01:25:15,812 --> 01:25:18,272
For the house?

1093
01:25:18,355 --> 01:25:22,023
I understand what
you were trying to do, but...

1094
01:25:22,107 --> 01:25:25,734
my wife's moving,
she's taking the boys.

1095
01:25:25,776 --> 01:25:28,318
The house is a little bit
too much for me right now.

1096
01:25:29,485 --> 01:25:30,944
I'm sorry.

1097
01:25:34,113 --> 01:25:36,406
I was a horribly unstable father.

1098
01:25:39,532 --> 01:25:42,492
And Valerie says
I'll never see them again.

1099
01:25:44,867 --> 01:25:46,786
But you know what?

1100
01:25:48,119 --> 01:25:49,536
I will.

1101
01:25:55,246 --> 01:25:59,166
I'll see 'em in a year or two...

1102
01:25:59,249 --> 01:26:00,667
may be three.

1103
01:26:03,293 --> 01:26:06,545
I'll go to Portland,
I'll call her...

1104
01:26:08,253 --> 01:26:11,046
and I'll find a way
to be their father again.

1105
01:26:16,214 --> 01:26:17,756
How about you?

1106
01:26:21,801 --> 01:26:23,884
Well...

1107
01:26:23,968 --> 01:26:26,594
I have the file...

1108
01:26:26,677 --> 01:26:28,763
but I don't need it anymore.

1109
01:26:33,680 --> 01:26:36,099
It's been taken care of.

1110
01:26:36,140 --> 01:26:38,850
You know.
It never happened.

1111
01:26:43,770 --> 01:26:47,437
But it did happen. Right?

1112
01:26:48,980 --> 01:26:50,396
Right.

1113
01:26:54,983 --> 01:26:56,942
So, now what?

1114
01:27:16,993 --> 01:27:21,037
I'm going to dinner with my wife...

1115
01:27:21,120 --> 01:27:22,537
her parents.

1116
01:27:25,205 --> 01:27:30,958
And this weekend,
I'm gonna go look at a boat.

1117
01:27:37,919 --> 01:27:43,421
And then on Monday, I'm gonna
come back in here and go to work.

1118
01:27:44,339 --> 01:27:45,755
And then...

1119
01:27:47,756 --> 01:27:49,757
magically this whole...

1120
01:27:51,800 --> 01:27:55,010
incredible day just somehow...

1121
01:27:55,052 --> 01:27:56,635
becomes a memory.

1122
01:27:59,512 --> 01:28:02,930
It's like you go to the beach.
You go down to the water.

1123
01:28:03,013 --> 01:28:06,474
It's a little cold.
You're not sure if you wanna go in.

1124
01:28:07,931 --> 01:28:09,975
There's a pretty girl
standing next to you.

1125
01:28:10,058 --> 01:28:13,809
She doesn't wanna go in either.
She sees you.

1126
01:28:13,851 --> 01:28:15,810
And you know...

1127
01:28:15,852 --> 01:28:19,188
if you just asked her
her name...

1128
01:28:21,856 --> 01:28:24,356
you would leave with her.

1129
01:28:24,398 --> 01:28:28,067
Forget your life,
whoever you came with...

1130
01:28:30,693 --> 01:28:32,652
and leave the beach with her.

1131
01:28:36,028 --> 01:28:37,946
And after that day...

1132
01:28:39,363 --> 01:28:41,989
you remember her.

1133
01:28:42,031 --> 01:28:46,909
Not every day, every week.

1134
01:28:48,701 --> 01:28:50,662
She comes back to you.

1135
01:28:52,411 --> 01:28:55,621
It's the memory...

1136
01:28:55,705 --> 01:28:57,622
of another life...

1137
01:28:57,705 --> 01:28:59,289
you could've had.

1138
01:29:02,707 --> 01:29:04,626
Today is that girl.

1139
01:29:29,553 --> 01:29:33,012
I'm sorry about what I did.

1140
01:29:37,472 --> 01:29:39,598
Me too.

1141
01:29:41,767 --> 01:29:43,726
You brought the file back.

1142
01:29:59,775 --> 01:30:04,276
When you're done, there's a lovely
little place on the hill where-

1143
01:30:04,360 --> 01:30:06,278
where you can get a-

1144
01:30:07,445 --> 01:30:09,196
- Cappuccino.
- Yes, that's right, dear.

1145
01:30:09,238 --> 01:30:12,698
They're lovely cappuccinos,
and it's clean and it's cool.

1146
01:30:12,740 --> 01:30:17,033
They have these prints on the wall.
They're really quite lovely.

1147
01:30:17,075 --> 01:30:21,327
I don't know who they're by.
They're by that artist-

1148
01:30:21,409 --> 01:30:24,287
- Chagall.
- Right. They're Chagalls.

1149
01:30:24,370 --> 01:30:26,120
There's three of them.
They're early Chagalls.

1150
01:30:26,203 --> 01:30:28,372
I think he painted them
when he was visiting there.

1151
01:30:35,792 --> 01:30:38,001
Am I missing something this evening?

1152
01:30:38,085 --> 01:30:40,545
- What is this?
- This, my dear-

1153
01:30:40,628 --> 01:30:43,879
This is Simon Dunne's...

1154
01:30:43,921 --> 01:30:46,881
power of appointment.

1155
01:30:46,923 --> 01:30:48,464
- I got it back.
- No, you didn't.

1156
01:30:48,547 --> 01:30:52,799
- Yes, I did. This is it.
- Please.

1157
01:30:52,882 --> 01:30:58,135
This is behind us, isn't it?
Haven't we put this behind us?

1158
01:30:58,218 --> 01:30:59,760
I was thinking about
what you said to me.

1159
01:30:59,843 --> 01:31:03,595
About the end of the day-
about doing more good than harm.

1160
01:31:03,679 --> 01:31:04,971
That is what you said, isn't it?

1161
01:31:05,055 --> 01:31:08,724
- Don't you fuck with me.
- I am not fucking with you, sir.

1162
01:31:10,016 --> 01:31:11,391
Can you imagine how unpleasant
it would be...

1163
01:31:11,474 --> 01:31:13,601
if the judge
got ahold of this file?

1164
01:31:13,643 --> 01:31:16,267
That's not gonna happen.
That's not gonna happen, Gavin.

1165
01:31:19,145 --> 01:31:22,771
I think I might order the snapper.

1166
01:31:25,981 --> 01:31:28,148
I'm gonna hold onto this file. I'm
gonna keep it in a very safe place.

1167
01:31:28,231 --> 01:31:30,942
But I'm not going to Texas.

1168
01:31:31,025 --> 01:31:33,277
I'm gonna come back
into work on Monday.

1169
01:31:33,360 --> 01:31:37,445
I'm gonna start doing that pro bono
work that you recommended that I do.

1170
01:31:37,529 --> 01:31:40,196
But I'm gonna do it
from our office.

1171
01:31:40,280 --> 01:31:44,281
The first thing we're gonna do
is help a man buy a house.

1172
01:31:44,322 --> 01:31:46,323
- Gavin, can we please not do this?
- And I think...

1173
01:31:46,365 --> 01:31:49,617
I would like to be the one
to call Mina Dunne.

1174
01:31:49,700 --> 01:31:51,660
I'm gonna tell her
that you and Walter...

1175
01:31:51,701 --> 01:31:54,785
are gonna give back the three
million dollars you stole...

1176
01:31:54,827 --> 01:31:56,786
from her grandfather's foundation.

1177
01:32:05,875 --> 01:32:09,626
You were right.
I can do this.

1178
01:32:09,668 --> 01:32:11,627
I found the edge.

1179
01:32:12,795 --> 01:32:14,420
Can you live there with me?

1180
01:32:17,213 --> 01:32:18,798
Can you?

1181
01:32:25,758 --> 01:32:28,217
I haven't had a fucking thing
to eat all day, and I'm starving.

1182
01:32:32,762 --> 01:32:34,971
So what are we gonna eat?

1183
01:32:53,770 --> 01:32:56,355
- Mrs. Gipson?
- Yes?

1184
01:32:56,439 --> 01:32:58,941
My name is Gavin Banek.

1185
01:32:59,024 --> 01:33:00,942
What do you want?

1186
01:33:02,066 --> 01:33:04,776
Five minutes, ma'am.

1187
01:33:04,860 --> 01:33:07,068
I owe your husband twenty.

1188
01:33:07,152 --> 01:33:09,362
Hell...

1189
01:33:09,445 --> 01:33:11,947
I'm only asking for five with you.

